Maintainer: Joana da Matta <joana.damatta02@gmail.com>
Description: Provides tools for predicting and evaluating intensive care unit (ICU) length of stay using machine learning methods.
  Includes functions for data preprocessing, feature selection, multiple imputation by chained equations (MICE), model training with stacking ensembles, and performance evaluation.
  The package facilitates reproducible ICU efficiency benchmarking and supports flexible model retraining and customization across healthcare datasets.
  It is based on the methodologies proposed by Peres et al. (2022, 2023), which utilize data-driven approaches for modeling and validation, offering insights into ICU performance and patient outcomes. References: Peres et al. (2022)<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35988701/>, Peres et al. (2023)<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37922007/>. 
  More information: <https://github.com/igor-peres/ICU-Length-of-Stay-Prediction>. 
